==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*hursaz'' (perhaps from a form ''*hrussa-'' ‘runner, racer’), from Indo-European ''*kers-'' ‘run’.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''hors'', Old Saxon [[hros]] (Dutch [[ros]]), Old High German [[hros]], [[ros]] (German [[Ross]]), Old Norse [[hross]] (Old Swedish ''hors''); and, outside the Germanic languages, with Latin [[currere]] ‘run, race’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /hors/

